description.narrative: A total of 40 target districts are currently implementing adolescent friendly health services with UNICEF support, an increase from 25 districts at the beginning of the current Country Programme. Up to 290,074 adolescents aged 10–19 years have received an HIV test with marked gender differentials showing greater uptake among females. Treatment coverage among ALHIV is low withslightly above 50 per cent of the estimated 90,000 ALHIV on life saving ART. | Status:Met | As-of Date:07/01/2022
